  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How I recover my Facebook password?",
  "response": "Recovering your Facebook password is a straightforward process. Follow the steps below to regain access to your account:\n\n### **1. Go to the Facebook Login Page**\n- Open your web browser and navigate to [facebook.com](https://www.facebook.com/) or open the Facebook app on your mobile device.\n\n### **2. Click on \"Forgot Password?\"**\n- On the login page, locate and click the **\"Forgot password?\"** link below the password field.\n\n### **3. Identify Your Account**\n- You will be prompted to find your account. Enter the email address, phone number, full name, or username associated with your Facebook account.\n- Click **\"Search\"** to locate your account.\n\n### **4. Choose a Recovery Option**\n- Facebook will display a list of options to send a password reset code. These options may include:\n  - **Email**: Send a code to your registered email address.\n  - **SMS**: Send a code to your registered mobile number.\n  - **Other methods**: Depending on your account settings, there might be additional options.\n- Select your preferred recovery method and click **\"Continue.\"**\n\n### **5. Retrieve the Reset Code**\n- Check your email inbox or SMS messages for the reset code sent by Facebook.\n- If you don't see the code, ensure you check your spam or junk folders. If you still haven't received it, you may need to try a different recovery option.\n\n### **6. Enter the Reset Code**\n- Input the code you received into the designated field on Facebook's recovery page.\n- Click **\"Continue.\"**\n\n### **7. Set a New Password**\n- After verifying the code, you will be prompted to enter a new password.\n- Choose a strong and unique password that you haven't used before on Facebook.\n- Confirm the new password by entering it again.\n\n### **8. Complete the Process**\n- Click **\"Continue\"** to finalize the password reset.\n- You may be asked to log out of other devices for security purposes. Follow the on-screen instructions as needed.\n\n### **Additional Tips:**\n\n- **Secure Your Account:** After regaining access, consider enabling **Two-Factor Authentication (2FA)** for added security. This requires a second form of verification when logging in.\n  \n- **Update Contact Information:** Ensure that your email address and phone number associated with your Facebook account are up to date. This makes future password recovery easier.\n  \n- **Use a Strong Password:** Create a password that includes a mix of letters (both uppercase and lowercase), numbers, and special characters to enhance security.\n\n- **Beware of Phishing Attempts:** Always ensure you're on the official Facebook website or app when entering your credentials. Avoid clicking on suspicious links or providing your password to untrusted sources.\n\n### **If You Can't Recover Your Account:**\n\nIf you're unable to reset your password using the above steps, consider the following:\n\n- **Visit Facebook's Help Center:** Go to [Facebook Help](https://www.facebook.com/help/) for more detailed assistance.\n  \n- **Report a Login Issue:** You can report problems directly to Facebook through their support channels.\n  \n- **Check Trusted Contacts:** If you've set up Trusted Contacts, you can reach out to them for assistance in recovering your account.\n\nBy following these steps, you should be able to successfully reset your Facebook password and regain access to your account. If you continue to experience issues, contacting Facebook Support directly is recommended.",
